This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) category as it deals with recommender systems, which are commonly used in information retrieval applications. The paper also proposes a novel method for modeling user preferences, which involves attention mechanisms and metric learning, both of which are popular topics in machine learning and natural language processing, which are covered by the Learning (cs.LG), Computation and Language (cs.CL), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories.
